<br>
When I say if we invade that terrorists will multiply, I mean that we will kill hundreds of people whose sons and daughters will probably grow up hating America for making them fatherless.  For every one terrorist you kill, you have the potential of making another 2.<br>
<br>
Also, have you heard what we're doing over there now?  If there's even a rumor about a possible terrorist cell or something like that in a place, they bomb the shit outta it, even if there are innocents there.  This is how far we're willing to go and I guarantee the terrorists are willing to go another foot farther.  I believe that we are multiplying terrorists.  (and before you call bullshit on what we're doing, I have a buddy over there in Iraq right now that I chat with whenever I can, he is the one that told me this)<br>
<br>
To answer your question I don't know what I would have done, ok?  You wanna hear that?  I'm sure you do.  I don't know, ok?  I don't have all the information and therefore cannot have made any kind of rational conclusion about it.  A situation like this is very precarious and requires information that I do not have.  Were I to go purely on instinct and my morals and feelings, I would have invaded, which you obviously didn't read in my last post.  But the situation is MUCH MUCH more complicated than a simple &quot;feeling.&quot;  I wish it were that easy, but it isn't.<br>
<br>
I can, however, tell you what I wouldn't do though.  I wouldn't snub my nose at the world, stumble around trying to get a gov't in place in Iraq, and scream &quot;Bring it on!&quot; bravely behind a podium 10,000 miles away from the action while the troops that I sent over there are over there dying by the dozens. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113883">Landale Palemoon (THE KING OF PANTS!!!)</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
